#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:5
msgid "CXL Device Hotplug"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:7
msgid ""
"Device hotplug refers to *physical* hotplug of a device (addition or removal "
"of a physical device from the machine)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:10
msgid ""
"BIOS/EFI software is expected to configure sufficient resources **at boot "
"time** to allow hotplugged devices to be configured by software (such as "
"proximity domains, HPA regions, and host-bridge configurations)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:14
msgid ""
"BIOS/EFI is not expected (**nor suggested**) to configure hotplugged devices "
"at hotplug time (i.e. HDM decoders should be left unprogrammed)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:17
msgid ""
"This document covers some examples of those resources, but should not be "
"considered exhaustive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:21
msgid "Hot-Remove"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:22
msgid ""
"Hot removal of a device typically requires careful removal of software "
"constructs (memory regions, associated drivers) which manage these devices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:25
msgid ""
"Hard-removing a CXL.mem device without carefully tearing down driver stacks "
"is likely to cause the system to machine-check (or at least SIGBUS if memory "
"access is limited to user space)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:30
msgid "Memory Device Hot-Add"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:31
msgid ""
"A device present at boot may be associated with a CXL Fixed Memory Window "
"reported in :doc:`CEDT<acpi/cedt>`.  That CFMWS may match the size of the "
"device, but the construction of the CEDT CFMWS is platform-defined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:35
msgid ""
"Hot-adding a memory device requires this pre-defined, **static** CFMWS to "
"have sufficient HPA space to describe that device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:38
msgid "There are a few common scenarios to consider."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:41
msgid "Single-Endpoint Memory Device Present at Boot"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:42
msgid ""
"A device present at boot likely had its capacity reported in the :doc:"
"`CEDT<acpi/cedt>`.  If a device is removed and a new device hotplugged, the "
"capacity of the new device will be limited to the original CFMWS capacity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:46
msgid ""
"Adding capacity larger than the original device will cause memory region "
"creation to fail if the region size is greater than the CFMWS size."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:49
msgid ""
"The CFMWS is **static** and cannot be adjusted.  Platforms which may expect "
"different sized devices to be hotplugged must allocate sufficient CFMWS "
"space **at boot time** to cover all future expected devices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:54
msgid "Multi-Endpoint Memory Device Present at Boot"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:55
msgid ""
"Non-switch-based Multi-Endpoint devices are outside the scope of what the "
"CXL specification describes, but they are technically possible. We describe "
"them here for instructive reasons only - this does not imply Linux support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:59
msgid ""
"A hot-plug capable CXL memory device, such as one which presents multiple "
"expanders as a single large-capacity device, should report the **maximum "
"possible capacity** for the device at boot. ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:72
msgid ""
"Limiting the size to the capacity preset at boot will limit hot-add support "
"to replacing capacity that was present at boot."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:76
msgid "No CXL Device Present at Boot"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:77
msgid ""
"When no CXL memory device is present on boot, some platforms omit the CFMWS "
"in the :doc:`CEDT<acpi/cedt>`.  When this occurs, hot-add is not possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:80
msgid ""
"This describes the base case for any given device not being present at boot. "
"If a future possible device is not described in the CEDT at boot, hot-add of "
"that device is either limited or not possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:84
msgid ""
"For a platform to support hot-add of a full memory device, it must allocate "
"a CEDT CFMWS region with sufficient memory capacity to cover all future "
"potentially added capacity (along with any relevant CEDT CHBS entry)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:88
msgid ""
"To support memory hotplug directly on the host bridge/root port, or on a "
"switch downstream of the host bridge, a platform must construct a CEDT CFMWS "
"at boot with sufficient resources to support the max possible (or expected) "
"hotplug memory capacity. ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:103
msgid ""
"For example, a BIOS/EFI may expose an option to configure a CEDT CFMWS with "
"a pre-configured amount of memory capacity (per host bridge, or host bridge "
"interleave set), even if no device is attached to Root Ports or Downstream "
"Ports at boot (as depicted in the figure above)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:110
msgid "Interleave Sets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:113
msgid "Host Bridge Interleave"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:114
msgid ""
"Host-bridge interleaved memory regions are defined **statically** in the :"
"doc:`CEDT<acpi/cedt>`.  To apply cross-host-bridge interleave, a CFMWS entry "
"describing that interleave must have been provided **at boot**.  Hotplugged "
"devices cannot add host-bridge interleave capabilities at hotplug time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:119
msgid ""
"See the :doc:`Flexible CEDT Configuration<example-configurations/flexible>` "
"example to see how a platform can provide this kind of flexibility regarding "
"hotplugged memory devices.  BIOS/EFI software should consider options to "
"present flexible CEDT configurations with hotplug support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:125
msgid "HDM Interleave"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:126
msgid ""
"Decoder-applied interleave can flexibly handle hotplugged devices, as "
"decoders can be re-programmed after hotplug."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/cxl/platform/device-hotplug.rst:129
msgid ""
"To add or remove a device to/from an existing HDM-applied interleaved "
"region, that region must be torn down an re-created."
msgstr ""
